[[File:Guangzhou Gymnasium.JPG|thumb|Guangzhou Gymnasium]] '''Baiyun New Town''' ({{zh|s=白云新城}}) is a new [[central business district]] (CBD) in [[Baiyun District, Guangzhou|Baiyun District]], [[Guangzhou]], [[China]], located around the [[Guangzhou Baiyun International Airport (former)|former Baiyun Airport]].
The CBD will be divided into six new [[communities]]: Huangshi ({{zh|s=黄石}}), Xiaogang ({{zh|s=萧岗}}), Jichang (Airport) ({{zh|s=机场}}), Yunshan ({{zh|s=云山}}), Chuangyi ({{zh|s=创意}}) and Keziling ({{zh|s=柯子岭}}). Xiaogang Village in the CBD will be [[redevelopment|redeveloped]]. New [[parks]] will be built around [[Baiyun Mountain (Guangdong)|Baiyun Mountain]], including Feixiang Park to the south and Community Park to the west. New [[buildings]] will be constructed, including an [[exhibition centre]], the Guangdong Painting Academy, the Guangzhou Museum and the Guangdong Performance Centre.
==Transport== For [[transportation]], [[Guangzhou Metro]] Line 2 and Line 14 will cut across the CBD.<ref>[http://en.olympic.cn/news/olympic_news/2009-02-10/1732339.html Baiyun New Town to have 13 parks by Asian Games]</ref><ref>[http://www.newsgd.com/pictures/construction/content/2009-02/06/content_4890108.htm Baiyun New Town, Guangzhou's new CBD to the north]</ref>
